## **User Stories**

---

### **Paper Submission & Management**

1. As a student, I want to submit an arXiv URL so I can start summarizing a paper.
2. As a student, I want to see my papers displayed in a **grid view** so I can easily find and select the one I want to work on.
3. As a student, I want papers to be **automatically processed** (fetched and split into chapters) so I don’t have to manually prepare them.
4. As a student, I want to receive a **notification** when my paper is ready to summarize so I know when to start.
5. As a student, I want to sort my papers by **publication date, title, or completion percentage** so I can prioritize my work.
6. As a student, I want to see the **completion percentage** on each paper’s folder icon so I can track my progress at a glance. A chapter counts as complete when a summary has been submitted for it.

---

### **Reading Phase**

7. As a student, I want to view chapters in a **carousel** so I can navigate between them easily.
8. As a student, I want to **start the reading phase** for a specific chapter so I can begin the exercise.
9. As a student, I want a **3-second countdown** before the reading phase starts so I can prepare mentally.
10. As a student, I want to read a chapter with a **timer** (1 minute per 100 words, adjusted by difficulty) so I can practice time-pressured reading.
11. As a student, I want to **adjust the difficulty level** (0.5x, 1x, 2x base time) so I can control the challenge.
12. As a student, I want a **visible warning at 30 seconds remaining** so I can prepare to transition to writing.
13. As a student, I want to **pause the reading timer** so I can take a break if needed.
14. As a student, I want the reading screen to **blur** when paused so I cannot continue reading while the timer is stopped.
15. As a student, I want to **resume the timer** so I can continue reading where I left off.
16. As a student, I want the reading screen to be **distraction-free** (no navigation, minimal UI) so I can focus on the content.
17. As a student, I want to customize the reading interface (font size, font type, dark mode, line spacing, margins) so it is comfortable for me.

---

### **Writing Phase**

18. As a student, I want the app to **automatically transition** to the writing phase when the reading timer ends so I can start summarizing immediately.
19. As a student, I want to **manually transition** to the writing phase so I can start summarizing when I am ready.
20. As a student, I want a **full-screen, distraction-free writing interface** so I can focus on my summary.
21. As a student, I want a **character/word counter** so I know how much I have written.
22. As a student, I want a **word limit** (default: 10% of the chapter’s word count) so I practice writing concisely.
23. As a student, I want a **warning** (red counter) when I exceed the word limit so I know to revise my summary.
24. As a student, I want a **writing timer** of at least 2× the reading time, **with a minimum floor of 3 minutes**, so I always have enough time to write thoughtfully regardless of chapter length.

---

### **Evaluation & Feedback**

25. As a student, I want to receive **streaming feedback token-by-token via Server-Sent Events (SSE)** so I can read it as it is generated.
26. As a student, I want to see a **loading indicator** during feedback generation so I know the system is working.
27. As a student, I want to see a **star rating (1–5)** for my summary so I can quickly gauge my performance.
28. As a student, I want to see **3-paragraph feedback** (Understood, Misunderstood, Missed) so I can learn from my mistakes.
29. As a student, I want to see the **reference summary** after receiving feedback so I can close the learning loop.

---

### **Post-Submission & Progress Tracking**

30. As a student, I want to view **all my summaries for a paper in one place** so I can review my work.
31. As a student, I want to see the **completion status** of each chapter (completed/incomplete) so I can track my progress.
32. As a student, I want to see the **last grade (star rating) and feedback** for each chapter so I can track my improvement.
33. As a student, I want to **relaunch the reading/writing sequence** for a chapter so I can retry and improve my summary.
34. As a student, I want to **export my summaries** as TXT or Markdown so I can use them for notes or sharing.

---

### **Settings & Accessibility**

35. As a student, I want to **toggle dark mode** so I can reduce eye strain.
36. As a student, I want to **adjust font size and spacing** so the text is comfortable to read.
37. As a student, I want my **settings to persist via localStorage** so I don’t have to reconfigure them each session.
38. As a student, I want the app to be **responsive** so I can use it on my laptop or mobile device.

