### **Database Schema**

> **Note:** Two fixes applied from v1.0:
>
> 1. `'order'` renamed to `'chapter_order'` to avoid SQL reserved-word conflicts.
> 2. `reference_summary` column added to `chapters` — the v1.0 schema had no storage for LLM-generated reference summaries, forcing expensive re-generation on every evaluation.

```sql
-- Papers
CREATE TABLE papers (
  id          SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  arxiv_id    TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  title       TEXT NOT NULL,
  authors     TEXT[],
  url         TEXT NOT NULL,
  status      TEXT DEFAULT 'pending',  -- 'pending', 'processed', 'error'
  created_at  TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Chapters
CREATE TABLE chapters (
  id                 SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  paper_id           INTEGER REFERENCES papers(id),
  title              TEXT NOT NULL,
  content            TEXT NOT NULL,
  word_count         INTEGER NOT NULL,
  chapter_order      INTEGER NOT NULL,  -- renamed from 'order' (reserved keyword)
  reference_summary  TEXT               -- LLM-generated; stored after processing
);

-- User Summaries
CREATE TABLE user_summaries (
  id             SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  chapter_id     INTEGER REFERENCES chapters(id),
  summary_text   TEXT NOT NULL,
  word_count     INTEGER NOT NULL,
  attempt_number INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,  -- increments on retry
  score          INTEGER,   -- 1-5 stars
  feedback_text  TEXT,      -- 3-paragraph LLM feedback
  created_at     TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);
-- Query latest attempt: ORDER BY attempt_number DESC LIMIT 1
```

